<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ally2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ally,</orth> vb., used only in the partic. <emph>allied</emph> == related: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.339" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 339</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.182" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 182</bibl> (Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> and most M. Edd. <emph>trained</emph>). In a more general sense == joined: <cit><quote>neither allied to eminent assistants,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 61</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>